ABOUT.comment: Header for a general description, e.g. of a user, or of iNaturalist itself

About-the-DQA-description: Tingkat Kualitas merangkum akurasi, presisi, kelengkapan, relevansi, serta kelayakan dari suatu pengamatan iNaturalist sebagai data keanekaragaman hayati. Beberapa atribut ditentukan secara otomatis, sementara beberapa atribut lain bergantung kepada suara pengguna iNat. iNaturalist membagikan pengamatan-pengamatan "Tingkat Riset" yang berlisensi dengan beberapa mitra data untuk keperluan sains dan konservasi.

Accessibility label for bulk import / photo import button

date-format-long.comment:
Date formatting using date-fns
Used for things like User Profile join date
See complete list of formatting styles: https://date-fns.org/v2.29.3/docs/format

date-format-month-day.comment:
Used when displaying a relative time - in this case, shows only month+year (same year) - e.g. Jul 3
See complete list of formatting styles: https://date-fns.org/v2.29.3/docs/format

date-format-month-year.comment:
Use when only showing an observations month and year
See complete list of formatting styles: https://date-fns.org/v2.29.3/docs/format

date-format-short.comment:
Short date, e.g. on notifications from over a year ago
See complete list of formatting styles: https://date-fns.org/v2.29.3/docs/format

Date-Range.comment: Label for controls over a range of dates

DATE-RANGE.comment: Label for controls over a range of dates

datetime-difference-days.comment: Used when displaying a relative time - in this case, X days ago (e.g. 3d = 3 days ago)

datetime-difference-hours.comment: Used when displaying a relative time - in this case, X hours ago (e.g. 3h = 3 hours ago)

datetime-difference-minutes.comment: Used when displaying a relative time - in this case, X minutes ago (e.g. 3m = 3 minutes ago)

datetime-difference-weeks.comment: Used when displaying a relative time - in this case, X weeks ago (e.g. 3w = 3 weeks ago)

datetime-format-long.comment:
Longer datetime, e.g. on ObsEdit

datetime-format-short.comment:
Shorter datetime, e.g. on comments and IDs
